Edits applied directly to `content/papers/propagation.in.waveguides.md`.

Summary of changes:
- Fixed a broken prose/citation segment:
  - `Mikaelyan[^7] and recently Chevalier,` -> `Mikaelyan[^7] and recently Chevalier[^8].`
- Improved markdown structure/readability with explicit blank-line paragraph separation around key transitions (including figure placeholders and nearby prose/equation blocks).
- Added visible equation-number tags to resolve all in-text Eq. references:
  - `\tag{1}`, `\tag{2}`, `\tag{9}`, `\tag{10}`, `\tag{11}`, `\tag{12}`, `\tag{13}`, `\tag{14}`, `\tag{15}`
- Removed unused metadata-style footnotes `[^1]`, `[^2]`, `[^3]` (non-body affiliation/presentation notes).
- Corrected an intermediate duplication so Eq. (12) appears once, correctly tagged.

Self-check completed:
- Paragraph boundaries intended as paragraph breaks are blank-line separated.
- All in-text equation references `(1), (2), (9), (10), (11), (12), (13), (14), (15)` resolve to display equations with visible numbers.
